Halve @Demi-Baguette{2} lengthwise and toast.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add @Fully Cooked Beef Meatballs{8%oz} and cook, stirring occasionally, until warmed through and browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @Italian Seasoning{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning; we sent more!

Stir in @Marinara Cup{5%oz} and a splash of water. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce is warmed through, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Top bottom baguette halves with meatballs and sauce. Sprinkle meatballs with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}. Close subs.

Divide subs between plates and serve.